<TITLE> Storm lashes Daulatdia </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bhola, May 25 (bdnews24.com) A cyclonic storm lashed over 300 houses at Doulatkhan Upazila in Bhola on Monday. Bhola deputy commissioner said the storm hit at around 9:30am over the southern region. People were asked to stay in safe shelter. Under the influence of the cyclone storm Aila over the north Bay, the coastal district has been asked to show danger signal number 7. Bashir Ahmed, deputy director at Red Crescent Society's cyclone preparedness programme for Bhola region said Dhalchar, Char Kukrimukri, Charpatila, Char Hasina, Char Nizam and Char Kachchhapia remained eight to ten feet under water. The people of those areas were being evacuated to safe shelters. Water Development Board's executive engineer Md Ferdous said a huge area was inundated after the dam of Hamidpur area of Char Fashion Upazila and Sakutia of Monpura upazila collapsed. bdn
